description: This file specifies the interface for the SNMP plugin in an advanced networking component. It declares external API functions and conditional macros for platform-specific DLL import/export directives, providing function prototypes for initializing, supporting object checks, and unloading the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_Init
methods.description: Initializes the SNMP plugin with maximum supported version and plugin information pointer.

methods.name: COSA_Async_Init
methods.description: Performs asynchronous initialization of the SNMP plugin.

methods.name: COSA_IsObjectSupported
methods.description: Checks if a specific SNMP object is supported.

methods.name: COSA_Unload
methods.description: Unloads or cleans up the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_MemoryCheck
methods.description: Performs a memory check for diagnostics.
